description:
The Micromundos project (2020) is conceived by Felipe Correia, a Brazilian photographer and visual artist, who creates, from photography and digital interventions, a futuristic, wild universe of technological reality, brings restlessness to abstraction and shows how it is possible to create the big worlds with little things. it is the first phase of the artist's vast research, starting with macrophotography.

This work was made with soap bubbles, macrophotography and lots of psychedelia.

